Problem

After selling a stock, you cannot buy on the next day.

You must wait 1 day.

What's Different?

Suppose we're holding a stock.

Normally (Stock II)

Sell today

↓

Tomorrow can buy
prices[i] + solve(i+1,1)

But now...

Sell today

↓

Tomorrow = Cooldown

↓

Day after tomorrow can buy

So after selling,

we jump i+2 instead of i+1

That's literally the entire problem.


class Solution {
public:
    int maxProfit(vector<int>& prices) {

        int n = prices.size();

        vector<int> ahead1(2, 0); // dp[i+1]
        vector<int> ahead2(2, 0); // dp[i+2]
        vector<int> curr(2, 0);

        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {

            // Can Buy
            curr[1] = max(-prices[i] + ahead1[0],ahead1[1]);

            // Holding
            curr[0] = max(prices[i] + ahead2[1],  ahead1[0]); // Cooldown
            

/after evry itertaion tehres a swicth
            ahead2 = ahead1;
            ahead1 = curr;
        }

        return ahead1[1];
    }
};
